Abuja (Sundiata Post) –   University of Ibadan (UI) has released the results of its Post-Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination (UTME) screening exercise for candidates who chose the institution. This is contained in a statement by the institution’s Director of Public Communications, Mr Olatunji Oladejo, in Ibadan on Saturday. Oladejo stated that the Registrar, Mrs Olubunmi Faluyi, announced the release of the results via the university’s Official Bulletin No. 4372 of Saturday, 17 April, 2021. Candidates were advised to check the admission portal for the results. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) recalled that the computer-based screening exercise took place from Tuesday, April 6 to Saturday, April 10, 2021. (NAN) The University of Ibadan, UI Post-UTME screening form for the 2017/2018 academic session is out.  UI cut-off mark for admission is 200. All candidates who made University of Ibadan their choice institution and score the required cut-off mark should apply for admission screening exercise. This is to inform candidates who… In "Education" The management of University of Ibadan (UI)has released the result of the 2017/2018 Post-UTME Screening exercise. Candidates who took part in the screening are to check their results using the steps below; How To Check UI Post-UTME Result 1. Go to http://admissions.ui.edu.ng/#/ 2. Enter your username and Password in the… In "Education" The University of Ibadan, UI has released the 2016 post-UTME/admission screening result for the 2016/2017 academic session. The Management of the Institution have made available the result strictly to the candidates that participated in the screening exercise for the 2016/2017 academic session. How To Check your UI Admission Screening Result… In "Education"